.cs 4 on
.item 'SET TIMER Command' 'Updated 12/14/84 by AEH'
.boxon
SET TIMER m.n
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SET TIMER commands interrupts an ORVYL program at the specified
time interval and displays the total program CPU time usage up to
that point.  "m" is seconds and "n" is tenths of a second.

This command helps you keep track of how much CPU time an ORVYL
program uses.  To turn the timer off, use the command SET TIMER 0.
The SHOW TIMER command displays the time set on the ORVYL timer.
.cs 4 off
